Javascript Object:

Car:

Properties: specify something
Wheels:4
Name:Alto
Weight:1000kg
Color:White
Variant:LXI


Actions: (Methods) : perform some task
Start
Stop
Drive
Brake

var x=10;
var name='raghu';
var wheel=4;
var name='alto';.....

var myCar={name:'alto',wheels:4,weight:1000;color:'white'} ==> Objects

var x=10;
x ==> 10;

var myCar={name:'alto',wheels:4,weight:1000;color:'white'}
myCar.name ==> alto
myCar.Name ==> undefined
myCar.wheels ==> 4
myCar.color ==> white
myCar["color"] ==> white

Javascript Events:
Events are something that can be applied to HTML elements

Button: 
Click event ==> invoke a function and that will execute some logic
<button id="myBtn" onclick="event or function_name">Click</button>

Load event:
window.onload = function_name; 

Dropdown ==> on selection of an option ==> selection change in the dropdown
<select id="myDropdown" onchange="function_name">
	<option>Option 1</option>
	<option>Option 2</option>
	<option>Option 3</option>
</select>


onclick
Events:
onchange
onload
onkeydown
onkeyup
onkeypress
